    "attributes": {
        "action": "Reduce timeframe insurance companies can use expired points against motorists",
        "additional_details": "Currently if you receive points that expire in 3 years insurance companies demand to inform them for 5 years. This is just a way to boost premiums. Let\u2019s change the law so that once points expire they cannot be used against you by insurance companies. \r\nPoints valid for 3 years stay on licence for 4 only for court information, a driver should not have to declare them once they reach the expiry date.",
        "background": "Insurance companies demand drivers to declare penalty points after the law states they have expired,",
